<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-436-600  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 436 600.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  May 14 1990 v7 n19 p73(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tool set offers developers integrated SQL environment. (SQLSolutions Inc.'s SQL Advantage) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pallatto, John.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>SQL Solutions Inc has introduced the SQL Advantage editor and SACompanion systems-administration tools.andP;  Both packages offerdevelopers a fully integrated programming environment aimed atcreating Structured Query Language (SQL) data base applications.andO;The two products enable developers to have a level of controlequal with that of third-generation language developmentenvironments in mainframe computers.andP;  SA Companion manages allaspects of SQL applications-development projects, while SQLAdvantage enables programmers to edit a program in one window andswitch to another window to compile and test the program.andP;  SACompanion is priced at $5,000 and up, and SQL Advantage starts at$7,500.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   SQL Solutions Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   SQL Advantage (Program development software) (productintroduction)SA Companion (Network management software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionProgram Development ToolsSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By John PallattoandM;SQL Solutions Inc. has assembled a tool set that offers developers a fullyintegrated programming environment tuned to create Structured Query Language(SQL) database applications.andM;The new SQL Advantage editor and SA Companion systems-administration tool,both available now, offer programmers a level of control on par with that ofthird-generation language development environments found on mainframes, saidDan Cronin, vice president of marketing for SQL Solutions in Burlington,Mass.andM;SA Companion outfits programming supervisors with the administration toolsnecessary to manage all aspects of SQL applications-development projects,Cronin said.andP;  With it, supervisors can keep track of development resources;manage user access to hardware peripherals, software tools and data; andgenerate reports on system usage and database capacity, he explained.andM;Beta testers of SQL Advantage applauded its ability to display multiplewindows, a capability that speeds the development process by reducing thenumber of steps needed to locate and correct bugs.andM;&quot;With [SQL Advantage], a developer can edit a program in one window andswitch to another window to test and compile another program,&quot; explained JohnGeier, application development manager with Shaw Data Systems Inc., asoftware consulting firm in Boston.andP;  Typically, developers must switch to andfrom the editor to perform these tasks, he said.andM;Also compelling is SQL Advantage's ability to emulate popular programeditors, allowing developers to work in familiar environments, Geier said.andM;Initially, SQL Solutions' tool set will support Sybase Inc.'s SQL Serverdatabases running on Sun Microsystems Inc.andP;  Unix workstations and DigitalEquipment Corp.andP;  VAX/VMS minicomputers, Cronin said.andP;  Later this year, aversion will follow for Microsoft Corp.'s SQL Server and for Oracle Corp.andO;databases on Unix and VAX/ VMS platforms, he said.andM;In 1991, SQL Solutions will bolster the line again with versions for IBM'sDB2 mainframe database, as well as Digital's Rdb and Ingres Corp.'s namesakeminicomputer databases, he added.andM;SQL Advantage is priced from $7,500 to $35,000, and SA Companion from $5,000to $25,000, depending upon the computer and number of users.andM;SQL Solutions, an independent subsidiary of Sybase Inc., can be reached at(617) 270-4150.andO;</TEXT></DOC>